50|$|In {{literary}} works, Taprobana {{was mentioned}} in Tommaso Campanella's The City of the Sun, written in 1602. Jorge Luis Borges mentions {{the island in}} the story The Lottery in Babylon in the collection The Garden of Forking Paths (1941) of his book Fictions (1944). Toprobana is the fictional location of the sky elevator in Arthur C. Clarke's science fiction novel The Fountains of Paradise (1979). British rock band My <b>Vitriol's</b> 2001 debut album Finelines features a track called Taprobane, courtesy of the band's lead singer Som Wardner who is of Sri Lankan origin.|$|R
